    {
      "number": 4,
      "id": "PR_kwDORWyibc7T-D5v",
      "title": "Editorial",
      "url": "https://github.com/bwesterb/draft-westerbaan-tls-keyshare-recommendations/pull/4",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "muhammad-usama-sardar",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "- s/I/We\r\n- Don't need to expand the CRQC abbreviation in security considerations again (already done in intro)",
      "createdAt": "2026-04-20T13:41:41Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-04-27T10:47:04Z",
      "baseRepository": "bwesterb/draft-westerbaan-tls-keyshare-recommendations",
      "baseRefName": "main",
      "baseRefOid": "1a6b21a24df573bf7f2ec0f16287f6530061b123",
      "headRepository": "bwesterb/draft-westerbaan-tls-keyshare-recommendations",
      "headRefName": "sec-cons",
      "headRefOid": "01a8073f914ccc448a232407b2e23e1d08d4544f",
      "closedAt": null,
      "mergedAt": null,
      "mergedBy": null,
      "mergeCommit": null,
      "comments": [
        {
          "author": "bwesterb",
          "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
          "body": "These edits are good, except the last edit \r\n\r\n> Remove unnecessary claim on \"after arrival of CRQC\", which is irrelevant to the draft.\r\n\r\nCan you explain why it's irrelevant? It seems pretty relevant to me that there is also an active attack if you keep non-PQ keyshares around.",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-26T09:14:10Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-04-26T09:14:10Z"
        },
        {
          "author": "muhammad-usama-sardar",
          "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
          "body": "> Can you explain why it's irrelevant? It seems pretty relevant to me that there is also an active attack if you keep non-PQ keyshares around.\r\n\r\nTechnical argument: I don't think there is any such attack for hybrids that you mention. Hybrids have the PQ part in KEM. So I believe when CRQC arrives, it's unnecessary to carry the baggage of traditionals along, but I don't see any active attack.\r\n\r\nNon-technical argument: In the current form, we are only recommending PQ in this draft. I think the attack -- if any -- would be relevant when we set the traditionals to not recommended etc.",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-26T20:59:19Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-04-26T20:59:19Z"
        },
        {
          "author": "bwesterb",
          "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
          "body": "The first sentence that you keep talks about the risk of _not_ using a PQ/T hybrid. The second sentence is a second attack that you're vulnerable to if you're not using a PQ/T hybrid. If you think the second sentence doesn't make sense, then the first one doesn't either.",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-27T09:35:20Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-04-27T09:35:20Z"
        },
        {
          "author": "muhammad-usama-sardar",
          "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
          "body": "Apologies, I misunderstood it. Fixing the PR.",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-27T10:43:12Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-04-27T10:43:12Z"
        }
      ],
      "reviews": []
    }
  ]
